{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "There is a problem generating pssm shadows when the directional light vector is perpendicular to ogre camera's direction vector. This causes an assert failure (Issue #470) which is also reproduceable in Ogre itself.\r\n\r\nThe workaround sets gazebo's LightMaker to create a non-unit-z directional light. This also happens to remove artifacts seen on the ground plane.\r\n\r\n\r\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>There is a problem generating pssm shadows when the directional light vector is perpendicular to ogre camera's direction vector. This causes an assert failure (Issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/470/crash-when-adding-a-directional-light-into\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Crash when adding a directional light into a scene that has a camera sensor\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#470</s></a>) which is also reproduceable in Ogre itself.</p>\n<p>The workaround sets gazebo's LightMaker to create a non-unit-z directional light. This also happens to remove artifacts seen on the ground plane.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Directional light workaround", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Directional light workaround</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "There is a problem generating pssm shadows when the directional light vector is perpendicular to ogre camera's direction vector. This causes an assert failure (Issue #470) which is also reproduceable in Ogre itself.\r\n\r\nThe workaround sets gazebo's LightMaker to create a non-unit-z directional light. This also happens to remove artifacts seen on the ground plane.\r\n\r\n\r\n", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/287/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diffstat/osrf/gazebo:091e2f1c9179%0D972e25123462?from_pullrequest_id=287"}, "commits": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/287/commits.json"}, "self": {"href